I grant my Agent the following powers to act on my behalf:

{{powers_granted}}

These powers shall include, where applicable, the authority to execute documents, enter into agreements, and take any and all actions that I could take myself in connection with the powers granted above.

In addition to the specific powers granted above, my Agent shall have the authority to:

(a) Access and manage my financial accounts, including banking, investment, and retirement accounts;
(b) Pay my bills, debts, and obligations;
(c) File tax returns and manage tax matters on my behalf;
(d) Manage, sell, or acquire real and personal property;
(e) Enter into, modify, or terminate contracts on my behalf;
(f) Engage professionals, including attorneys, accountants, and financial advisors, as needed.

This Power of Attorney does not authorize the Agent to:

(a) Make, amend, or revoke my will or any codicil thereto;
(b) Make decisions regarding my healthcare, unless specifically authorized;
(c) Exercise powers for the Agent's own benefit, except as specifically authorized;
(d) Transfer my assets to the Agent without fair consideration;
(e) Perform any act that is contrary to my known wishes or best interests.

The Agent accepts the appointment and agrees to:

(a) Act in the Principal's best interest at all times;
(b) Avoid conflicts of interest;
(c) Keep accurate records of all transactions conducted on behalf of the Principal;
(d) Keep the Principal's property separate from the Agent's own property;
(e) Act within the scope of authority granted by this document.
